This paper deals with the use of Golay sequences in OFDM, which is a topic related to information theory and communication (cs.IT, cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the construction of cosets of Reed-Muller codes, which is a topic related to coding theory and algebraic geometry (cs.DS). The application of the theory to PAPR under the Walsh-Hadamard transform suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI).
